OFFICE OF THE VICE-PRESIDENT (TEACHING AND LEARNING)
Senior Project Manager - Digital Transformation (23240931)
The appointee will be responsible for planning and implementation of digital transformation initiatives related to teaching and learning with the aim to enhance users’ experience, improve operational efficiency, and facilitate data-driven decision-making to achieve the Vision and Mission of the University. 
Responsibilities:
Support the Project Director for the development and implementation of the Student Lifecycle Management System (SLCMS) and other teaching and learning-related projects under the University’s digital transformation initiative: 
Lead and supervise a team to ensure successful implementation;
Act as a major liaison person internally and externally;
Be responsible for the tendering and procurement processes;
Work with user departments and the Office of Information Technology (ITO) to assess, consolidate, and validate the user requirements from concept to execution, develop fit-for-purpose processes, data management systems, and cater information/reporting needs;
Work with user departments and the Office of Information Technology (ITO) to devise a plan for the incorporation/integration of the existing systems with the solutions provided by the contractor(s);
Work with internal parties and external consultant(s)/contractor(s) on the user specifications, design development, testing, user training and system enhancement; and
Monitor outsourcing contractors’ performance to ensure quality, timeliness, and fulfillment of the user requirements within budgetary constraints.

Requirements:
A bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related discipline;
At least 10 years of project management/consulting experience and demonstrated track record in leading large-scale projects for the higher education sector; experience in other sectors will also be considered;
A self-starter with a strong sense of commitment and ability to work under pressure; 
Ability to translate needs analysis data into formal designs, and strong organisational, interpersonal, and problem-solving skills; and 
Excellent communication skills in spoken and written English and Chinese.

The initial appointment will be made on a fixed-term contract of three years.  Re-appointment thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement, availability of funding and project needs. 
Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.
